<TITLE> KU VC panel selected </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 8 (bdnews24.com)  A government search committee has formed a recruitment panel of three potential candidates for the post of Khulna University vice chancellor. Some 45 applications were submitted for the position, an education ministry official told bdnews24.com. "A panel of three eligible candidates for the appointment of vice chancellor has been selected," the search committee's member secretary AZM Shafikul Alamtold bdnews24.com after a meeting on Monday. "The list will be sent to the chancellor and he will select one," said Alam, who is also joint secretary of the education ministry. Professor Saifuddin Shah is currently holding the KU VC post on a temporary basis after Prof Mahbubur Rahman resigned. The education ministry formed a search committee on July 29 last year in line with a 1973 ordinance to appoint VCs, pro-VCs and treasurers for all public universities, except those of Dhaka, Rajshahi, Jahangirnagar and Chittagong. bdnew
